  "prompt": "Are there any apps which offer similar information with the sociometric badges used by MIT's media labs?",
  "response": "While I'm not aware of exact replicas of MIT Media Lab's sociometric badges, there are some apps and technologies that provide similar social interaction and workplace analytics:\n\n1. Humanyze (founded by ex-MIT Media Lab researchers)\n- Uses wearable badges to analyze workplace communication\n- Provides insights on team interaction and collaboration patterns\n\n2. Workplace Analytics (Microsoft)\n- Analyzes communication and collaboration through Office 365 data\n- Provides insights on team dynamics and productivity\n\n3. Slack Analytics\n- Measures communication patterns within teams\n- Provides data on message frequency, channel engagement\n\n4. Organisational Network Analysis (ONA) Tools\n- Examples: TrustSphere, Workplace Relationship Intelligence\n- Analyze communication networks and interaction patterns\n\n5. Wearable Technology\n- Some enterprise wearables track movement, proximity, and interaction\n- Examples: Fitbit workplace solutions, Garmin workplace tracking\n\nThese tools don't exactly replicate sociometric badges but offer similar insights into workplace interactions, communication patterns, and team dynamics.\n\nThe closest equivalent to MIT's original research would likely be Humanyze, as it was directly spun out of the MIT Media Lab research on sociometric badges.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these technologies?",
